===Etymology===
Latin ''[[vivus]]'' alive + English [[section]]: compare French ''vivisection''.  See [[vivid]], and [[section]]

===Noun===
'''vivisection'''

#the action of [[cutting]], [[dissect|dissecting]] or other painful treatment of a living [[organism]] for the purposes of [[physiology|physiological]] or [[pathology|pathological]] scientific investigation.  The term is mainly used by opponents of animal research.

